Website Terms of use
for SilhouetteAmerica.com
1. Acceptance of terms
Silhouette America, Inc. ("Silhouette America®", "we", "us", "our") makes available to
                        you (the user) our website (
www.silhouetteamerica.com
) subject to these
                        Terms of Use, which may be modified from time to time at our sole discretion, with or without
                        notice to you.
Your use of this website, now or in the future, indicates acceptance of the
                        then-current Terms of Use. You agree to abide by all of the Terms of Use, as the same may be
                        revised from time to time. Silhouette America® may offer other services that may be governed by
                        additional or different terms.
2. Description of services
Silhouette America® provides you access to the Silhouette America® website so long as
                        you have agreed to the Terms of Use. Access to select sections of this website require you to
                        log into a Silhouette Account. The creation of a Silhouette Account is free and holds no
                        obligation to purchase of goods or services. You can continue to access these sections requiring
                        you to be signed into your account so long as your account is active. Such access may be
                        modified, revised, updated, enhanced, or supplemented by Silhouette America® from time to time.
3. Silhouette user account
As a condition of using the sections of the website which require you to sign into a
                        Silhouette account, you must be at least eighteen (18) years or older, an emancipated minor, or
                        possess legal parental or guardian consent, and are fully able and competent to enter into the
                        terms and conditions set forth in these Terms of Use. In any case, you affirm that you are over
                        the age of thirteen (13).
You agree to: (a) provide accurate, current, and complete information about yourself
                        as prompted by the account registration form, and (b) maintain and promptly update the
                        registration data to keep it accurate, current and complete.
You will create a password and account designation during the account's registration
                        process. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of the password and account,
                        and are fully responsible for all activities that occur under your password or account.
                        Silhouette representatives are unable to ask for or receive passwords for your Silhouette
                        account. If you need to reset your account password or account email address, or merge duplicate
                        user accounts, you may contact Silhouette Support for assistance. Silhouette Support can only
                        assist with such requests upon successful verification of account ownership.
You understand that if supplied, your credit card number is stored on your Silhouette
                        account as a token only. The full credit card number is not stored on any Silhouette server
                        either in raw or encrypted format. Upon creating or editing any credit card information on your
                        Silhouette account, you authorize Silhouette America® to send your encrypted credit card data to
                        a third party processor for secure storage. You understand that Silhouette representatives do
                        not have access to your credit card data beyond the card type, expiration date, and last four
                        digits of the card. Silhouette representatives are unable to ask for or receive credit card
                        information for your Silhouette account. You are solely responsible for maintaining accurate
                        credit card information on your Silhouette account and you alone are able to add or edit credit
                        card information.
You understand that you may be contacted regarding your account status or account
                        activity, including purchases made, your subscription status, or balances owed. Notification
                        preferences can be controlled under your account settings at
Silhouette America
Any order history, services, memberships, and information stored on your account,
                        including software license keys, cannot be transferred to other accounts. Your account may not
                        be shared, transferred, sold, or given to any other individual.
4. Collection and use of personal data
The Silhouette America® Privacy Policy protects your personal identity data from
                        disclosure, and Silhouette America® agrees to comply with all aspects of the Privacy Policy. All
                        data that is not personally identifying may be used, disclosed, manipulated, aggregated,
                        disaggregated, sold, shared, or distributed by Silhouette America® for any purpose.
5. Club Silhouette Program
Club Silhouette memberships are a premium service offered by Silhouette America® which provide special services and considerations to club members, including monthly digital content, periodic product shipments, and discounts on orders placed at
www.silhouetteamerica.com
A membership to Club Silhouette is not required to access the Silhouette America® website. You must have a Silhouette account in order to sign up for a Club Silhouette Membership at Join Club Silhouette.
You must have a Silhouette account in order to sign up for a Club Silhouette Membership at
Join Club Silhouette
.
A. Trial Membership Option
Club Silhouette entitles you to the 30-Day Free Trial membership for thirty days from the moment that you activate the free trial period, which you do when you submit your payment details. When you submit these payment details, you accept the 30-Day Free Trial Offer and accept that we use your payment details according to our Privacy Policy. You also agree to the Silhouette America 30-Day Free Trial Terms and Conditions. If you decide to discontinue the Club Silhouette 30-Day Free Trial upon or any point prior to the lapse of the free trial period, you will need to discontinue the 30-Day Free Trial membership before the free trial period ends.
Once ended, the Free Trial cannot be reinstated, even if canceled in error. You may not use this 30-Day Free Trial more than once.
B. Continuing Membership After Trial
If you do not discontinue the 30-Day Free Trial membership before the free trial period ends, you will be charged a Club Silhouette membership fee depending on the membership type selected during the sign up process. A yearly (12-month) membership can be purchased for $9.99 per month. Customers selecting to pay up-front for a yearly (12-month) membership can purchase a yearly subscription at $99.99, meaning that an additional discount is given to customers who choose to pay their subscription up-front at sign up rather than month-to-month.
C. Club Silhouette Membership
Silhouette America can only ship to areas listed under section 20 “Shipping” of these Terms of User. If you do not reside in any of the designated areas, Silhouette America cannot mail you free products offered through the Club Silhouette program.
Club Silhouette offers three free shipments during the course of the year-long Club Silhouette membership of a blade (or Mint Stamp Kit) and mat (or Mint Stamp Sheet set). You are responsible for maintaining a current valid mailing address in order to accurately receive free refill items offered through the Club Silhouette program. Any changes to your mailing address must be made at least 24 hours in advance of your scheduled shipment or your scheduled shipment may be issued to a previous mailing address provided.
Shipping times for free products are subject to availability. Silhouette America® is not liable for late shipments of regularly scheduled shipments through the Club Silhouette program. If your selected free product is not available at the time of your scheduled shipment, you may be offered the option to change your product selection to an alternate product approved by Silhouette America®. Returns or exchanges are not accepted for free products received through the Club Silhouette program.
Club Silhouette membership discounts exclude Silhouette machines, Silhouette Mint™ products, clearance item products, downloads, download cards, subscriptions to the Silhouette Design Store, and gift cards. Club Silhouette membership discounts will be automatically applied to all orders placed at www.silhouetteamerica.com and can be combined with sales promotions except where specifically excluded in the Terms and Conditions of the promotional sales event. Club Silhouette membership must be active prior to placing any order for the Club Silhouette membership discount to apply. The Club Silhouette membership discount cannot be applied retro-actively to any orders preceding membership.
The “free shipping” perk available with Club Silhouette only pertains to orders placed through the Silhouette America® website at www.silhouetteamerica.com for orders which exceed a $50 subtotal, where the order amount exceeds $50 prior to any additional taxes and/or shipping costs. Club Silhouette membership must be active prior to placing any order for the Club Silhouette membership free shipping perk to apply. The Club Silhouette membership free shipping perk cannot be applied retro-actively to any orders preceding membership.
Club Silhouette membership offers 10 digital content designs on the 15th of each month. Silhouette America® reserves the right to issue this content within 10 business days of the expected delivery date. These designs are offered only in STUDIO or STUDIO3 file format for use with the Silhouette Studio® software application. All digital content is selected by Silhouette America®. Returns or exchanges of digital content are not accepted.
Silhouette America® reserves the right to discontinue or alter the Club Silhouette Terms and Conditions at any time without prior notice and with no liability. Further information on the Club Silhouette program may be found at
https://silhouetteamerica.freshdesk.com/en/support/solutions/articles/35000205987-club-silhouette-overview
.
D. Canceling Club Silhouette Membership
Club Silhouette membership will continue to auto-renew until it is canceled by the customer. Customers may select to cancel Club Silhouette Membership by logging into their Silhouette account at
www.silhouetteamerica.com
and visiting the "My Account" section. Customers may alternately contact the Silhouette America® Support Team (support@silhouetteamerica.com) to request their Club Silhouette membership be canceled. Club Silhouette membership may be canceled at any time.
Refunds are not available for the first month’s service, regardless of whether you had selected to pay month-to-month or if you had paid the up-front yearly amount, if a shipment of free product has been issued. You are responsible to end your Club Silhouette membership prior to the initial shipment of free product if you do not wish to be charged for the Club Silhouette membership service.
All Club Silhouette Points become forfeit upon cancellation of your Club Silhouette Membership.
E. Reinstating Club Silhouette Membership
Club Silhouette membership may only be reinstated by contacting Silhouette Support.
6. Educator Discount Program
The Educator Discount Program (“EDP”) provides a special discount on Silhouette products purchased directly through
www.silhouetteamerica.com
qualifying educational facilities and licensed non-profit organizations. The EDP is only valid in the United States and Canada. To apply, you must contact
education@silhouetteamerica.com
and relay a) your Silhouette account address, b) the name and location of your school or institution, and c) an attached eligible copy of your teaching certificate or 501(c)(3) form. You may be asked to provide updated information, as deemed necessary by Silhouette America®, at any time, which may affect your eligibility and participation in the EDP.
Acceptance to the EDP is at the sole discretion of Silhouette America®. Any order placed prior to acceptance to the EDP cannot be retro-actively refunded or credited. The EDP discount shall apply from the date and time of acceptance forward. By being accepted to the EDP, you are in no way obligated to fulfill any minimum purchase requirement. You may opt out of the EDP at any time without penalty by contacting Silhouette Support.
You understand that by being accepted to the EDP you have no additional rights granted to your Silhouette account beyond the ability to receive an additional discount on select regularly priced product offerings for purchases made directly through
www.silhouetteamerica.com
The discount provided through the EDP is only available on select product offerings and purchases made directly through
www.silhouetteamerica.com
The EDP discount shall be according to the information provided at the time of acceptance to the EDP. The EDP discount cannot be combined with any other programs, discounts, sales, pricing, or promotions. The EDP discount excludes digital content offered through the Silhouette Design Store
                    (
www.silhouettedesignstore.com
)Silhouette Design Store subscriptions, Silhouette Design Store download cards and codes, Club Silhouette Membership fees, Silhouette gift cards, and other select products as determined at the sole discretion of Silhouette America. Orders placed through the EDP are tax exempt.
By applying to the EDP you agree to all Terms and Conditions for the EDP stated in this section. Silhouette America® reserves the right to alter the EDP at any time with or without notice to you.
7. Silhouette Account Activity
Your Silhouette account will remain active until it is canceled by you via request to
                        Silhouette America® customer service, or until it is terminated by Silhouette America®.
8. Account Cancellation By You
You have the right to cancel your Silhouette account at any time, whereupon Silhouette
                        America® will have the right immediately to terminate your access to sections of the website
                        requiring you to log in, including any access to manage Silhouette Design Store subscription
                        options. Upon cancellation, you will not be entitled to a refund of any fees paid by you under
                        any circumstances. Upon termination, you will lose access to all purchase history, the ability
                        to recover purchased content from the Silhouette Design Store, and any license keys applied to
                        your account. You must contact Silhouette Support to cancel your account.
9. Account Termination By Silhouette America®
Silhouette America® shall have the right to terminate your password, account, or use
                            of the website (or any part thereof), at any time in its sole discretion, with or without cause
                            and with or without prior notice. If you already have paid subscription fees for any
                            subscription month and Silhouette America® terminates your access to the Silhouette Design Store
                            service during or prior to that subscription month, Silhouette America® will promptly return the
                            subscription fees you have paid for that month. If you have paid subscription fees for an entire
                            subscription year and Silhouette America® terminates your access to the Silhouette Design Store
                            service during the subscription year, Silhouette America® will return a prorated portion of the
                            subscription fees, based on the portion of the subscription year remaining as of the date of
                            termination. Except as provided in the preceding two sentences, Silhouette America® shall not be
                            liable to you for any termination of your access to the Silhouette Design Store service. Upon
                            termination, you will lose access to all purchase history, the ability to recover purchased
                            content from the Silhouette Design Store, and any license keys applied to your account.
